Collaborative Notes REST API

A backend application for creating and managing notes with multi-user collaboration, built using Node.js, Express, and PostgreSQL.
Users can securely create notes, share them with others, and control access using read/write permissions.

Features :

User authentication using JWT

Secure password hashing with bcrypt

Create, read, update, delete (CRUD) notes

Share notes with other users

Permission-based access:

Read → view only

Write → edit access

Middleware-based authorization

Transaction handling for sharing/unsharing notes

Tech Stack :

Backend: Node.js, Express

Database: PostgreSQL

Authentication: JWT

Security: bcrypt

API Testing: cURL / Postman

Setup Instructions : 
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/collaborative-notes.git
cd collaborative-notes
2. Install dependencies
npm install
3. Setup environment variables

Create a .env file:

KEY=your_jwt_secret
DATABASE_URL=your_postgres_connection_string
4. Run the server
node server.js

Live API : 

Deployed on Render:

https://collaborative-notes-mb3n.onrender.com

API Endpoints :
Auth
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/auth/signup	Register user
POST	/auth/signin	Login and get JWT
Notes
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/create	Create note
GET	/notes	Get all own notes
GET	/notes/:id	Get specific note
PUT	/notes/:id	Update note
DELETE	/notes/:id	Delete note
Sharing
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/notes/:id/shared	Share note
DELETE	/notes/:id/shared	Remove access
GET	/notes/:id/shared	View collaborators
GET	/shared	Notes shared with you

Authentication :

All protected routes require:

Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

Key Concepts Implemented :

Middleware-based authentication & authorization

Role-based access control (owner / read / write)

Transaction handling in PostgreSQL

Secure API design

Example Request
curl -X POST <baseurl>/signin \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d "{\"username\":\"pink\",\"password\":\"pp@2.\"}"

Future Improvements:

API documentation (Swagger/OpenAPI)

Docker containerization

Pagination & search

Rate limiting & security enhancements

Author:

Developed as a backend project to demonstrate API design, authentication, and multi-user collaboration.
